### Description

[JIRA](https://usebruno.atlassian.net/browse/BRU-2991)

Adds `@annotation` / `@annotation('value')` decorator syntax to `.bru` dictionary blocks. The Ohm grammar is extended with annotation rules (`annotation`, `annotationentry`, `pairannotations`) across `bruToJson.js`, `collectionBruToJson.js`, and `envToJson.js`. Annotations are attached via a hidden `Symbol` key and exposed as an `annotations` array on parsed pairs — only when present, preserving backward compatibility. Serializers (`jsonToBru.js`, `jsonToCollectionBru.js`, `jsonToEnv.js`) gain a `serializeAnnotations()` helper that handles no-arg, single-line (auto-quoting), and multiline (`'''`) cases, applied across all dictionary block paths. A comprehensive test suite (`annotations.spec.js`) covers parsing, serialization, and roundtrip correctness.

```bru
headers {
  @description('Auth token') authorization: Bearer {{token}}
  @required
  @string content-type: application/json
  @deprecated ~x-old-header: legacy
}

params:query {
  @description('Search term') q: hello
  @string ~limit: 10
}

assert {
  @description('Status check') res.status: eq 200
}

vars:pre-request {
  @description('Base API URL') baseUrl: https://api.example.com
  @deprecated ~oldVar: unused
}
```

